                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/810: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Canton</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pontius</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-25T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 23, 10 a.m.</p>
                <p>It is suggested that you should exercise caution in accepting messages of the
                    kind quoted in your telegram, which for obvious reasons this Government is
                    unable officially to transmit. You should, however, keep the Department fully
                    informed concerning the sentiment of the southern leaders.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
